      • structures

      • processesMap

        private java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,AndGuardOperator>>> processesMap
        Multiple nested maps as follows: processesMap : Process Name -> Process Map (A Map that represents the skeleton of that process). Process Map : From State (comma separated labels in alphabetical order) -> Out Going transitions Map for that state. Out Going transitions Map : To State (comma separated labels in order) -> The guard for moving between From State towards To State.

      • states

        private java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,SkeletonState> states
        The resulting states will be stored here. The mapping is from labels to State Object.

      • transitions

        private java.util.ArrayList<SkeletonTransition> transitions
        The resulting transitions will be stored here.

      • getCommonName

        public java.lang.String getCommonName()
        Returns:
        the common name between all structures being converted. The common name is the longest common prefix of all the structures names. For example: Mutex1(1, 2), Mutex2(2, 3), Mutex3(5, 6), etc; have a prefix in common "Mutex" which is the common name.
